results.start_instructions:
Welcome!

In this annotation task you will be marking up a PDF for someone to edit. At each page you will be instructed on what edits you're making on the PDF. Your goal is to find as many sections of the PDF that you think can be edited in the way you're instructed.

pages.instructions: In this annotation task you will be marking up a PDF for someone to edit. At each page you will be instructed on what edits you're making on the PDF. Your goal is to find as many sections of the PDF that you think can be edited in the way you're instructed.

tasks.instructions:
The goal is to reduce any sections that you feel are wordy.

  • Highlight as many sections of the PDF that you think can be made more concise.
  • Look for sections that you think can be written in fewer words.
  • If you think no section would benefit from being edited, do not highlight anything.

pages.instructions: In this annotation task you will be marking up a PDF for someone to edit. At each page you will be instructed on what edits you're making on the PDF. Your goal is to find as many sections of the PDF that you think can be edited in the way you're instructed.

tasks.instructions:
The goal is to make every section as clear and complete with details as needed.

  • Highlight as many sections of the PDF that you think can be made more elaborate.
  • Look for sections that you think can be written in more words or with more details.
  • If you think no section would benefit from being edited, do not highlight anything.

pages.instructions: In this annotation task you will be marking up a PDF for someone to edit. At each page you will be instructed on what edits you're making on the PDF. Your goal is to find as many sections of the PDF that you think can be edited in the way you're instructed.

tasks.instructions:
The goal is to turn bullet points to elaborate paragraphs.

  • Highlight as many sections of the PDF that you think can be edited from a list or bullet points to a paragraph.
  • If you think no section would benefit from being edited, do not highlight anything.

pages.instructions: In this annotation task you will be marking up a PDF for someone to edit. At each page you will be instructed on what edits you're making on the PDF. Your goal is to find as many sections of the PDF that you think can be edited in the way you're instructed.

tasks.instructions:
The goal is to make every section easier to skim.

  • Highlight as many sections of the PDF that you think would be easier to read if written as bullet points or a list.
  • If you think no section would benefit from being edited, do not highlight anything.

pages.instructions: In this annotation task you will be marking up a PDF for someone to edit. At each page you will be instructed on what edits you're making on the PDF. Your goal is to find as many sections of the PDF that you think can be edited in the way you're instructed.

tasks.instructions:
The goal is to make the document sound professional.

  • Highlight as many sections of the PDF that you think can be written in a more formal language.
  • If you think no section would benefit from being edited, do not highlight anything.

pages.instructions: In this annotation task you will be marking up a PDF for someone to edit. At each page you will be instructed on what edits you're making on the PDF. Your goal is to find as many sections of the PDF that you think can be edited in the way you're instructed.

tasks.instructions:
The goal is to make it the tone more casual.

  • Highlight as many sections of the PDF that you think can be written in more casual language.
  • If you think no section would benefit from being edited, do not highlight anything.

pages.instructions: In this annotation task you will be marking up a PDF for someone to edit. At each page you will be instructed on what edits you're making on the PDF. Your goal is to find as many sections of the PDF that you think can be edited in the way you're instructed.

tasks.instructions:
The goal is to make it as easy as possible for anyone to understand.

  • Highlight as many sections of the PDF that you think can be written in more simple language.
  • If you think no section would benefit from being edited, do not highlight anything.

pages.instructions: In this annotation task you will be marking up a PDF for someone to edit. At each page you will be instructed on what edits you're making on the PDF. Your goal is to find as many sections of the PDF that you think can be edited in the way you're instructed.

tasks.instructions: Thinking of the document as a whole. Select any types of edits you might want to apply to the whole document:
response_options: Change the tone from casual to formal
Change the tone from formal to casual
Reduce the length of the document to be more concise
Increase the length of the document to be more elaborate
Change the entire document into paragraph without any listing/bullet points
Change the entire document into bullet points/listing
user_response: Reduce the length of the document to be more concise

pages.instructions: Enter your username to submit the task.
